# What The Original Yamaha Safety Relay Did

The factory system had two internal relays:

## Relay 1 — Starter Cut-Off Relay (SR)

Purpose:
- Prevents accidentally pressing the starter button while the engine is already running

How it works:
- Engine stopped → starter works normally
- Engine running → relay opens starter circuit

---

## Relay 2 — Lighting Relay (LR)

Purpose:
- Prevents the headlight drawing power during startup
- Turns headlight on once engine is running
- Keeps headlight on until ignition is switched off

How it works:
- Engine stopped → headlight OFF
- Engine starts → headlight ON
- Engine stalls → headlight stays ON while key remains ON

---

# How This Replacement System Works

This replacement uses:

- Relay A = Starter Cut-Off Relay (SR)
- Relay B = Lighting Relay (LR)
- Diode = startup trigger isolation
- Resistor = headlight relay latch circuit

The yellow alternator wire triggers both relays once the engine starts generating AC voltage.

